## What you CAN do

- Read, study, and audit the source code
- Run nodes for research, education, and personal use
- Mine blocks on the Assentian-PQE testnet or mainnet
- Contribute improvements via pull request
- Build non-commercial tools, wallets, and experiments on top of this codebase
- Operate a public or private mining pool that mines against the live
  Assentian-PQE (SNTI) network, including running a stratum server,
  charging pool fees, and onboarding third-party miners

## What you CANNOT do (without written permission from the Licensor)

- Launch a competing PQ-PoW cryptocurrency using this codebase
- Fork, relicense, or repackage this codebase's mining/stratum
  components to sell as a standalone commercial mining-pool product
  or service (e.g. white-labeling this code for other coins)
- List a forked coin derived from this codebase on any exchange
- Use Assentian-PQE's XMSS-PoUW integration in a commercial product
  or service unrelated to operating against the genuine SNTI network

## After the Change Date (June 15, 2030)

This software will be re-licensed under GPL-2.0-or-later, at which point
all restrictions above are lifted and the code becomes fully open source.

## Foundation

This codebase is built on Bitcoin Core v27 (MIT License) and the XMSS
reference implementation (CC0/Public Domain). Those components retain
their original licenses. The Assentian-PQE-specific additions (XMSS
wallet integration, PoUW consensus, P2XMSS/P2XMSSHASH script types,
and related infrastructure) are covered by this BSL-1.1 license.

